I thoroughly enjoyed this piece. For those of you who are afraid to use your imagination, perhaps you should skip this movie If you don&#039;t like any philosophical dialogue, then potentially skip this too. However, if you have a penchant for movies with a darker aesthetic, with clever use of stylish violence (violence however, not being the adhesive which connects this movie together).

The use of different camera angles was quite entertaining, and I particularly thought that the casting was well done.

one thing that may have deterred most is the seeming &#039;off&#039; quality that a lot of the camera work has, but this personally did not detract from my experience.

In retrospect, I feel that this movie shares similarities with &#039;The Crow&#039;, in regards to many stylistic choices, and in some aspects of character development.
